					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">About switching mid-scanline, it's really not worth it. It would require so much annoying effort to try and do that, and you wouldn't end up with pretty results. I've often wondered about vertical split screen effects, but they're really hard to do.
<br />
<br />I too will be fine if we stick with smaller characters. It just seems like everyone wants large characters. What Bananmos was suggesting is a good idea, I think. I do this for my portraits in my game, where I have details made with sprites and the "base" part made with BG. Though I use multiple palettes for the base part.
<br />
<br />EDIT: You might not want to assume that each character will have lots of skin showing. Look at the character in my portrait. He has only his face and hands showing. The rest is a brown coat. Actually, that character is only made of 3 colors, and I don't think it's horribly obvious. Though you can tell by looking at it. He wouldn't require many palettes.</div>

